{
  "text": "The introduction of this H function allows to describe the \"close on flow\" property [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] of the valve. To describe the \"open on pressure\" property [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , another H function must be introduced in Equations 7 and 8, to allow blood flow (Q) from the time when upstream pressure is higher than downstream pressure, until the time when blood flow becomes negative. It is written. H((P up -P down ) + Q -0.5).",
